text: Abramovo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Abramovsky Selsoviet of Kuybyshevsky District, Novosibirsk Oblast, Russia. The population was 1222 as of 2010. There are 19 streets. == Ethnicity == The village is inhabited by Russians. == References == Category:Rural localities in Novosibirsk Oblast
title: Abramovo, Novosibirsk Oblast
